1
00:00:00,540 --> 00:00:02,070
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,740
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:05,110
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:07,480
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee,
Let Chloe Lee shape Adele's future.)

5
00:00:07,550 --> 00:00:10,250
After bringing Chloe on board,
Adele's stock has been soaring.

6
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:12,650
And Director Kim,
who made this deal happen,

7
00:00:12,650 --> 00:00:16,350
- has been named president...
- The genius who stayed hidden.

8
00:00:16,490 --> 00:00:19,090
The news of her appearance
is drawing global attention.

9
00:00:19,090 --> 00:00:20,260
Adele's move has been hailed
as brilliant.

10
00:00:20,260 --> 00:00:22,490
Everyone is wondering
who Chloe really is...

11
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:24,530
and why she picked Adele
as her partner...

12
00:00:24,530 --> 00:00:25,660
out of so many companies.

13
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:27,230
Her first project
gets revealed today...

14
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:28,230
Manager Jo.

15
00:00:28,870 --> 00:00:29,870
Yes?

16
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:37,040
She really is something else.

17
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:41,280
Looks like Director Kim landed
a real heavy hitter.

18
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:43,250
I can't believe this.

19
00:00:43,980 --> 00:00:46,920
This Chloe or whatever.
Why was she so easy to get?

20
00:00:47,490 --> 00:00:50,460
Of all people, why did she let
that tramp bring her here?

21
00:00:52,460 --> 00:00:53,630
Who is this woman, anyway?

22
00:00:55,530 --> 00:00:58,960
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee,
Let Chloe Lee shape Adele's future.)

23
00:01:00,470 --> 00:01:04,100
Goodness.
The genius shrouded in mystery.

24
00:01:04,170 --> 00:01:07,670
The world-renowned brand consultant,
Chloe Lee.

25
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,540
Chloe Lee.

26
00:01:10,580 --> 00:01:12,140
Judging by the name,
it must be a woman.

27
00:01:12,610 --> 00:01:15,050
I heard she's a workaholic
with crippling social anxiety.

28
00:01:15,210 --> 00:01:17,720
That's why
she's never been seen until now.

29
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:21,250
You're passing off your own hopes
as a rumor.

30
00:01:21,550 --> 00:01:24,920
Since you can't fault her skills,
you're painting her as a weirdo.

31
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:28,660
- Typical you.
- Those rumors aren't new.

32
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:31,830
You're a bit touchy.
Why so defensive?

33
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:35,830
Why are you so threatened by someone
you've never even met?

34
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:40,570
Are you just jealous?
Jealousy is admitting defeat.

35
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:42,740
You've already lost. Game over.

36
00:01:43,210 --> 00:01:44,710
- Director Kim!
- Director Kim!

37
00:01:44,810 --> 00:01:45,910
- Director Kim.
- Director Kim?

38
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,750
- It's Director Kim.
- Director Kim.

39
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,750
How did you convince Chloe to join?

40
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:51,680
What were the terms
of Chloe's contract?

41
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:53,490
Does this give you the upper hand
in the succession race?

42
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:55,290
Please comment on your strategy.

43
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:56,890
Is it true that Chloe
reached out to you first?

44
00:01:56,990 --> 00:01:58,190
A comment, please!

45
00:02:15,170 --> 00:02:16,570
Chloe has arrived.

46
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:19,110
- It's Chloe.
- Chloe?

47
00:02:19,610 --> 00:02:20,610
Are you Chloe?

48
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:22,780
It's Chloe!

49
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,580
Chloe, could you please
look over here?

50
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:27,720
Just one comment, please.

51
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:31,320
Could you say a few words?

52
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:35,330
- A quick comment, please.
- Chloe, a comment, please!

53
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:36,490
Please look this way.

54
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,160
- Over here, please.
- Chloe, any comment?

55
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,850
- Unbelievable.
- How could...

56
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:55,980
Baek Jin Ju?

57
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:05,890
Are you Director Kim Myung Hui
from the Adele Group?

58
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:11,000
I'm Chloe, the brand consultant.

59
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,130
A pleasure. I'm Kim Myung Hui.

60
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,210
Excuse me?

61
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:25,340
Could you both please make your way
to the stage?

62
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:28,180
Of course. I'll lead the way.

63
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:40,260
This is Choi Yu Na, the head
of the New Business Task Force.

64
00:03:53,970 --> 00:03:54,970
It's a pleasure to meet you.

65
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,040
I'm Chloe.

66
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:43,420
- Chairman Park!
- What is it?

67
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,560
Sir.

68
00:04:46,290 --> 00:04:48,030
What's all this commotion?

69
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:52,560
It's Baek Jin Ju. She's here.

70
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:54,070
Baek Jin Ju?

71
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:56,300
Who's that?

72
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:02,440
Chloe is Baek Jin Ju.
She's alive and she's back.

73
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:16,050
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee,
Let Chloe Lee shape Adele's future.)

74
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:27,300
This is
Executive Director Park Min Jun.

75
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,500
I look forward to working with you.

76
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,540
Jin Ju?

77
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,120
Gosh, you're gorgeous.

78
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:47,450
Thank you.

79
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,360
Are you really Chloe?

80
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:59,960
I'm not what the rumors say
about me, am I?

81
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:01,500
When's your birthday?

82
00:06:03,270 --> 00:06:04,270
So in Korea,

83
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:06,270
you ask someone's birthday
instead of saying hello?

84
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,980
Executive Director Park.

85
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:25,090
Shall we get on with the event?

86
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,430
I know you're shocked,
but get a grip, will you?

87
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,840
See how awkward this is getting?
Everyone's staring at us.

88
00:06:58,420 --> 00:06:59,420
This way, please.

89
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:04,800
What's the matter?

90
00:07:08,770 --> 00:07:10,600
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee,
Let Chloe Lee shape Adele's future.)

91
00:07:25,450 --> 00:07:28,050
We should stay for the event.
What's the rush?

92
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:31,360
I hate seeing Kim Myung Hui win.
It makes me sick.

93
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:34,190
And I'm certainly not going
to just sit here and applaud her.

94
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:38,160
We need to find a way
to sabotage her somehow.

95
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:46,340
Oh my, Chairman Park!

96
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:49,010
Move!

97
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:56,780
- Are you all right?
- Forget it.

98
00:07:57,450 --> 00:07:59,120
Seriously, what's his hurry?

99
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:02,920
He's with Ms. Choi.
Looks like they're off to the event.

100
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:06,020
Did he just push me aside
to go see Kim Myung Hui?

101
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:08,330
Now I'm pissed.

102
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:14,530
By the way, why is he always
dragging Ms. Choi around?

103
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,840
(Brand Consulting Agreement)

104
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:34,120
Thank you for partnering
with the Adele Group.

105
00:08:34,190 --> 00:08:35,620
The pleasure's all mine.

106
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:37,360
Thanks to you,

107
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:41,790
I'm now able to work
with the Adele Group.

108
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:46,760
Shall we finish up
with the photos, then?

109
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,000
(Park Min Jun, Park Hyun Jun)

110
00:09:41,490 --> 00:09:43,020
The deal is off.

111
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:48,630
There will be no deal whatsoever
with Adele Group.

112
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:53,030
No way. That's impossible.

113
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:58,000
That's right.
Of course you should recognize me.

114
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:02,510
That's the only way
I can truly savor...

115
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:04,880
coming back to you.

116
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:27,570
Chairman Park too?

117
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,840
Why is everyone acting so weird
around Chloe?

118
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:43,180
I'm sure it was Jin Ju.

119
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:44,550
Sure.

120
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:47,650
I'll admit,
the resemblance is uncanny.

121
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:50,760
Just a look-alike?

122
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:52,560
If she's not a look-alike,
what is she?

123
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,560
Is there some kind of birth secret?

124
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:56,390
Is she Jin Ju's long-lost twin?
Come on.

125
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:57,560
I'd rather believe...

126
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:59,060
it's one of the world's great mysteries.

127
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:03,470
It's more plausible
that a perfect doppelganger exists.

128
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,700
It felt like more than
just a resemblance.

129
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:09,370
I'm certain...

130
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:11,740
she's Jin Ju.

131
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,750
So what, did a dead person
come back to life?

132
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:17,920
That makes even less sense.

133
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,200
It's Jin Ju.

134
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,770
Others might not realize it,

135
00:11:41,940 --> 00:11:43,440
but I can tell.

136
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:47,380
Hey, I'm telling you it's not her!

137
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:12,240
Do you always stare at people
that intently?

138
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:18,980
Just kidding.

139
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,680
It's just that you were staring
so intensely.

140
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:29,150
No, it's just...

141
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:34,490
It's fascinating that such a genius
is a fellow Korean.

142
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:37,630
I was so glad to meet you...

143
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:40,060
that I was naturally drawn to you.

144
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,970
If I offended you,

145
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,500
I apologize.

146
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:47,070
The chairman...

147
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,670
has been very interested
in your work.

148
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:52,410
Really?

149
00:12:53,610 --> 00:12:55,250
So, on that note,

150
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,780
there's something
I'd like to ask you.

151
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,120
Of course. Go ahead.

152
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:04,620
You haven't shown your face
this whole time,

153
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:09,790
and I'm sure other companies
have made you better offers.

154
00:13:10,590 --> 00:13:12,730
So why are you
showing yourself now...

155
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,830
and partnering with Adele Group?

156
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:18,100
Because of Temi Bio.

157
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:26,240
If you're interested in my work,

158
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:29,050
you probably know
I'm very into biotech companies.

159
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:33,520
I also enjoy growing small startups
into major players.

160
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:36,520
Adele Group's bio division, however,

161
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:40,790
hasn't made any progress
since acquiring Temi Bio.

162
00:13:41,590 --> 00:13:44,500
I wanted to see just how much
I could turn things around,

163
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:46,500
and I couldn't resist the challenge.

164
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,040
As for why I decided
to reveal my identity,

165
00:13:57,040 --> 00:14:00,740
the paparazzi trying to get my photo
became too much to handle.

166
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:04,520
So I decided it was a good time
to come forward.

167
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,320
I see.

168
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:09,820
Of course,

169
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:13,820
I was also quite impressed
with Director Kim's proposal.

170
00:14:14,530 --> 00:14:16,690
I look forward
to your help and guidance.

171
00:14:18,060 --> 00:14:19,730
Of course. Absolutely.

172
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,320
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

173
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:44,320
Chloe, who on earth are you?

174
00:14:44,990 --> 00:14:46,390
Are you actually Chloe?

175
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,290
Or are you...

176
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:56,270
How can you two be so incompetent?

177
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:59,440
The Chloe project file
only contains contract terms,

178
00:14:59,970 --> 00:15:02,770
and there's absolutely
no personal information on her.

179
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:04,740
Well, that's...

180
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:08,910
There's no public information
to be found.

181
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:12,520
You know today was the first time
she ever revealed her identity.

182
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,150
That's why I'm telling you
to investigate and report back.

183
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:20,120
Her family, education, and career.
I want every last detail!

184
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:23,260
- Now.
- Yes, ma'am.

185
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,170
Baek Jin Ju is dead.

186
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:36,110
She definitely died in that fire.

187
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:42,910
Choi Yu Na.

188
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,120
Is that you, Yu Na?

189
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:47,720
Yu Na, please, you have to help me!

190
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:56,990
This isn't my fault.

191
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:01,670
Baek Jin Ju, you're the one...

192
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,040
who drove me to this.

193
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,310
Yu Na?

194
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,790
I'm not the one
who deserves the blame.

195
00:16:28,930 --> 00:16:30,390
It's Chairman Park Tae Ho!

196
00:16:35,930 --> 00:16:36,970
No.

197
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:40,270
Baek Jin Ju is dead. She has to be.

198
00:16:41,710 --> 00:16:43,310
If Chloe is Baek Jin Ju,

199
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,810
it's all over.

200
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:09,130
What are you doing here?

201
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:12,400
I'm just looking around.

202
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:15,370
You're looking around?

203
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:25,220
I'm sure I'm allowed
to look around the office.

204
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:30,090
After all, this is where
we'll be working together.

205
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:35,090
What do you mean,
we'll be working together?

206
00:17:36,090 --> 00:17:37,900
I spoke to the chairman.

207
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:41,400
Instead of using a large office
by myself,

208
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:44,170
I'd rather work alongside
the rest of the staff.

209
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:49,740
I heard the New Business Task Force
handles the bio division too.

210
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:54,910
I'll be officially working out
of this office starting tomorrow,

211
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:56,710
so let's try to get along...

212
00:17:59,150 --> 00:18:00,250
like friends.

213
00:18:03,390 --> 00:18:04,390
Friends?

214
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:09,730
Are you scared of me?

215
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,100
What the...

216
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:16,430
You've been acting that way
since the moment you saw me,

217
00:18:16,870 --> 00:18:19,170
as if you'd seen a ghost.

218
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:27,610
See? You're doing it again.

219
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:35,250
I'm not that scary, you know.

220
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:38,390
There's no way I'm a ghost, either.

221
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:44,660
It's not like I'm someone
who has come back from the dead,

222
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:47,600
right?

223
00:18:53,270 --> 00:18:55,010
I'll see you tomorrow.

224
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:19,000
I'm Chloe's agent, James Lee.

225
00:19:19,230 --> 00:19:22,030
Here's Chloe's background information,

226
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,800
so don't go making things up.

227
00:19:23,870 --> 00:19:25,970
Please stick to the facts
in your reports.

228
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:27,910
Please! Thank you.

229
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:40,920
We meet again.

230
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,490
We do?

231
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,960
Don't tell me you don't remember me.

232
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:48,930
I'm not exactly easy to forget.

233
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:02,810
Oh, right.

234
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:05,110
The clown in the white pants.

235
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:07,280
A clown?

236
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:15,320
What the...

237
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:18,920
Come on. Let me see that!

238
00:20:18,990 --> 00:20:21,290
This is a press kit.
It's for reporters only,

239
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:22,760
and you're not one.

240
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,420
Did something happen?

241
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:50,220
It was nothing.
Don't worry about it.

242
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,360
Sure.

243
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:58,100
Is this what Chloe's agent
gave the reporters?

244
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:01,160
Yes. I took a look,
but nothing stood out.

245
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:02,670
Really?

246
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:09,010
By the way, what did you make of it
when Chloe first showed up?

247
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:11,680
Didn't everyone seem a little off?

248
00:21:12,510 --> 00:21:16,480
Chairman Park, for one, along
with Ms. Choi and even Min Jun.

249
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:18,050
They weren't themselves.

250
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:21,520
Now that you mention it, it was odd.

251
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,690
Min Jun's reaction bugged me too.

252
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:27,890
There's definitely something
we don't know.

253
00:21:28,130 --> 00:21:31,060
Still, isn't it too risky
to dig into Chloe's past?

254
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:33,300
She was guarded
about her personal information...

255
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,560
in the contract, remember?

256
00:21:35,570 --> 00:21:38,970
That's why I'm going to keep an eye
on someone else, not Chloe.

257
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:40,840
Someone else?

258
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:52,850
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

259
00:21:58,020 --> 00:22:02,330
A dead ringer for Baek Jin Ju
who's also interested in Temi Bio?

260
00:22:03,330 --> 00:22:04,760
Can that be all just a coincidence?

261
00:22:10,130 --> 00:22:11,130
Come here.

262
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,710
Tell me straight.

263
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:19,440
Did you see
Baek Jin Ju die that day or not?

264
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:24,650
Why aren't you answering me?

265
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,320
I saw it.

266
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:31,620
Baek Jin Ju was in the car
when it exploded.

267
00:22:36,890 --> 00:22:39,030
What are the chances
that Chloe is Baek Jin Ju?

268
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:42,130
Zero.

269
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,200
Then why are you so terrified?

270
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,640
That's because...

271
00:22:51,010 --> 00:22:52,740
she looks exactly like Jin Ju.

272
00:22:54,380 --> 00:22:55,480
In any case,

273
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:58,920
now that you're sharing
an office with Chloe,

274
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:00,950
make sure you watch her closely.

275
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:04,760
And bring me proof
that Chloe is not Baek Jin Ju!

276
00:23:07,290 --> 00:23:10,160
Proof that she's not Baek Jin Ju?

277
00:23:36,390 --> 00:23:37,520
Are you all right?

278
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:39,890
Yes, I'm fine.

279
00:23:41,590 --> 00:23:44,830
By the way,
you seem a little off today.

280
00:23:45,630 --> 00:23:47,860
You seemed very surprised
to see Chloe.

281
00:23:50,670 --> 00:23:51,670
Was I?

282
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:53,970
Well, I wasn't.

283
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:56,840
Really?

284
00:23:58,110 --> 00:23:59,110
Then,

285
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:01,010
I'll be on my way.

286
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:13,390
Why did you run away
when Chloe appeared?

287
00:24:14,090 --> 00:24:17,730
Why did you bring Chairman Park
to face Chloe?

288
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:31,540
Let's try to get along...

289
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:35,080
like friends.

290
00:24:37,650 --> 00:24:38,980
Friends? As if.

291
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:43,950
Baek Jin Ju is dead.

292
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:46,920
She's just a look-alike.

293
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,090
I knew it.

294
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,330
Why were you eavesdropping?

295
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,670
I overheard you.

296
00:24:56,670 --> 00:24:58,670
If it was a secret,
you should've kept it to yourself.

297
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:04,040
You don't think
she's Baek Jin Ju either, right?

298
00:25:05,710 --> 00:25:06,740
Isn't it obvious?

299
00:25:12,250 --> 00:25:13,420
Then what's with that look
on your face?

300
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:15,190
What look?

301
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:19,060
I get why Min Jun looks out of it.
He thinks she's Baek Jin Ju.

302
00:25:19,260 --> 00:25:22,190
But you don't think it's her,
so why do you look so off?

303
00:25:25,630 --> 00:25:27,500
You look like you've seen a ghost.

304
00:25:30,470 --> 00:25:33,600
It's almost like you're scared
Baek Jin Ju is back from the dead.

305
00:25:36,270 --> 00:25:37,740
What are you talking about?

306
00:25:38,410 --> 00:25:40,640
Why would I be scared?

307
00:25:41,410 --> 00:25:42,450
And as for Chloe...

308
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:46,320
If you actually talk to her,
you'll see she's totally different.

309
00:25:46,820 --> 00:25:48,250
They just look a little alike.

310
00:25:48,250 --> 00:25:49,890
The way she thinks, speaks,
and carries herself...

311
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:51,760
It's all different.

312
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:52,790
Really?

313
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:56,190
You're saying Chloe and Baek Jin Ju
are two totally different people.

314
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,590
That's what I just said.

315
00:25:58,830 --> 00:26:00,330
Now stop bothering me and move.

316
00:26:10,540 --> 00:26:11,540
It's a pleasure to meet you.

317
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,480
I'm Chloe.

318
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:18,950
Min Jun isn't in a state
to see things clearly,

319
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:23,050
so Choi Yu Na's perspective
is probably the most reliable.

320
00:26:24,090 --> 00:26:26,260
They were friends for a long time.

321
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:28,430
So if she thinks this is someone
completely different,

322
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:29,860
then Chloe...

323
00:26:31,330 --> 00:26:32,500
must really just be Chloe.

324
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:39,170
So is this where Ms. Choi lives?

325
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,840
Yes, it is, but...

326
00:26:43,410 --> 00:26:45,210
I don't think this is a good idea.

327
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:47,880
How can you say that
after Kim Myung Hui's huge success?

328
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:53,250
While she's busy becoming president,
we need to snatch up her shares.

329
00:26:58,690 --> 00:26:59,690
But...

330
00:27:00,620 --> 00:27:02,630
But... Darn it.

331
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:07,260
What's for dinner tonight?

332
00:27:09,230 --> 00:27:10,230
Unbelievable.

333
00:27:10,970 --> 00:27:13,000
What do you think?
It's kimchi stew, of course.

334
00:27:17,540 --> 00:27:20,580
But we had kimchi stew
for breakfast and for lunch.

335
00:27:20,710 --> 00:27:22,550
Are we really
eating kimchi stew all day?

336
00:27:23,450 --> 00:27:24,480
Honestly.

337
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:28,850
What do you expect
when you have all your meals...

338
00:27:28,850 --> 00:27:30,450
in this house?

339
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:34,160
Stop living up to your name
and go out once in a while.

340
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,730
Unbelievable.

341
00:27:36,860 --> 00:27:40,330
Looking back,
we shouldn't have just taken shares.

342
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:43,470
You should've demanded
an executive position too.

343
00:27:43,470 --> 00:27:44,470
What a waste.

344
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:47,940
An executive position?
Why would I want that headache?

345
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:51,780
Our savings and shares
generate a steady income.

346
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:52,840
Please.

347
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:55,450
That small amount of income
is barely enough to live on.

348
00:27:55,780 --> 00:27:57,910
It'd be more than enough
if you didn't buy...

349
00:27:58,210 --> 00:28:00,180
ridiculous hats and clothes.

350
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:01,480
Why you...

351
00:28:03,750 --> 00:28:06,060
What? Who's here at this hour?

352
00:28:06,320 --> 00:28:07,320
What?

353
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:23,670
You're Adele Group's chairman's wife?

354
00:28:24,540 --> 00:28:25,540
That's right.

355
00:28:26,110 --> 00:28:30,510
I am the actual wife
of Adele's chairman, Park Tae Ho.

356
00:28:33,250 --> 00:28:36,490
Well, what brings you here?

357
00:28:37,820 --> 00:28:39,720
Let's become in-laws.

358
00:28:40,690 --> 00:28:41,690
Excuse me?

359
00:28:42,260 --> 00:28:43,260
What?

360
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:59,240
So, how was my welcome reception?

361
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:01,410
Fantastic.

362
00:29:03,010 --> 00:29:05,010
Loud and flashy, just as planned.

363
00:29:08,490 --> 00:29:11,720
And starting tomorrow,
things will get louder every day.

364
00:29:13,420 --> 00:29:14,420
Right.

365
00:29:23,870 --> 00:29:27,040
Looks like my welcome reception
isn't over yet.

366
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:42,820
Excuse me,

367
00:29:44,050 --> 00:29:45,120
do you have a moment?

368
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,150
What can I help you with?

369
00:30:10,150 --> 00:30:11,410
When's your birthday?

370
00:30:12,380 --> 00:30:13,480
Not this again.

371
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:15,550
Why are you so curious
about my birthday?

372
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:18,350
- Is it in the fall?
- The spring.

373
00:30:19,490 --> 00:30:20,490
Spring?

374
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:23,230
Since I was born
when everything was green and new,

375
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:27,060
my name is Chloe,
which means "green shoot" or "bloom."

376
00:30:27,500 --> 00:30:29,400
My father gave me the name.

377
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,770
Is your father still alive?

378
00:30:32,340 --> 00:30:34,540
Of course. He's in great health.

379
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:38,410
Then, can you make seaweed soup?

380
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,040
I don't cook.

381
00:30:41,810 --> 00:30:43,310
Do you happen to believe in fate?

382
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:44,750
No.

383
00:30:45,150 --> 00:30:46,880
I don't believe in things like that.

384
00:30:47,350 --> 00:30:48,380
Then,

385
00:30:50,090 --> 00:30:51,090
just this once,

386
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:53,990
may I hold you?

387
00:30:55,730 --> 00:30:56,730
Excuse me?

388
00:31:12,810 --> 00:31:16,080
You keep telling me I'm wrong,

389
00:31:17,550 --> 00:31:18,620
but my eyes,

390
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:20,780
my hands, and my heart...

391
00:31:22,390 --> 00:31:23,950
know what they feel.

392
00:31:26,460 --> 00:31:28,160
Are you not telling the truth,

393
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:31,090
or is my heart wrong?

394
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,200
Jin Ju.

395
00:31:52,750 --> 00:31:53,980
Why is Min Jun...

396
00:32:22,980 --> 00:32:25,950
(Pearl in Red)

397
00:32:26,080 --> 00:32:28,250
Just this once, may I hold you?

398
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:31,190
Don't you want to have some fun?
The hotter, the better.

399
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:33,920
Because of Chloe,
even Min Jun wasn't himself.

400
00:32:33,990 --> 00:32:36,890
You're glaring at me
like I did something wrong.

401
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:38,630
If you don't want to be exposed,
lie low.

402
00:32:38,700 --> 00:32:40,900
Not for your sake,
but for our Min Jun.

403
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,830
I'm sorry, but you won't
be able to protect anything.

404
00:32:45,800 --> 00:32:47,840
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
